722809f-a.title: Manhattan: Riverside Drive - 155th Street
722809f-a.text:
Riverside Drive, west side (actually north side, as the Drive forms
a sharp loop at this point) between West 155th and 158th Streets, showing
the interior of a triangular block formed by the Drive and West 158th
Street with its western edge facing the North (Hudson) River. Several
frame dwellings and numerous garages are located therein. Both of these
views are northward; No. 1 from on the West 156th Street line, and No. 2
from West 157th Street (alongside of No. 799 Riverside Drive, the frame
dwelling shown on the (rightlof Wo.1 In No. 2 are shown the rears of
Nos. 648 to 636 West 158th Street, a portion of a row of private dwellings
on the south side of the street and west of the Drive. The entrance to
this Village would be on the left of the tree.bearing sign.

722807f-a.title: Manhattan: Riverside Drive - 155th Street
722807f-a.text:
Riverside Drive, north from but not including 155th Street. This
view shows the viaduct, built at a cost of)2.000.000 which eliminates
a detour at 155th Street, and enables traffic to continue along the
''drive'' without interruption, to 200th Street.
About 1934.
Ewing Galloway.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
